cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the problem of terrain guarding, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of reduction from PLANAR 3-SAT, which is a problem in theoretical computer science, and hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves proving NP-hardness, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
